java
Copy
Edit
class MaxNestingDepth {
    public int maxDepth(String s) {
        int currentDepth = 0;
        int maxDepth = 0;

        for (char ch : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (ch == '(') {
                currentDepth++;
                maxDepth = Math.max(maxDepth, currentDepth);
            } else if (ch == ')') {
                currentDepth--;
            }
        }

        return maxDepth;
    }

    // Sample usage
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        MaxNestingDepth md = new MaxNestingDepth();
        System.out.println(md.maxDepth("(1+(2*3)+((8)/4))+1")); // Output: 3
        System.out.println(md.maxDepth("(1)+((2))+(((3)))"));   // Output: 3
        System.out.println(md.maxDepth("1+2*3/4"));             // Output: 0 (no parentheses)
    }
}
ðŸ’¡ Explanation:
Iterate over the characters in the string:

( increases the current depth.

) decreases it.

Track the maximum depth reached during traversal.

